FBIS3-34548 "drnes027_r_94004" FBIS-NES-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 SOUTH ASIA India Ministers Criticize Bhutto's `Propaganda Offensive' BK0802114394 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 GMT 8 Feb 94 BK0802114394 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The minister of state for home, Mr. P.M. Sayeed, has said that the Pakistani prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, is accusing India only to divert the people's attention from domestic problems. Speaking to newsmen at Thiruvananthapuram today, he said that Kashmir is an integral part of India and the government will initiate political process in the valley as soon as the law and order situation returns to normal. Meanwhile, the minister of state for external affairs, Mr. Salman Khurshid, has criticized the Pakistani prime minister's propaganda offensive against India.
